race.comment: They'll go like the clappers in this. COSMO CENTAURUS (12) has looked good in both runs this time in work and is two from two around this circuit. Should get a nice run just off the speed and will give backers a sight. POSTER GIRL (15) resumed with a strong win at Eagle Farm and winning rider Harley stays in the saddle. Drawn to get a cosy run in transit from the inside alley and can go back-to-back to start the campaign. BOSSED UP (19) has only missed a place once in four starts at this track and will be rock-hard fit for this. Not to be discounted lightly. COLOPHON (5) has put back-to-back wins together over this six-furlong trip and gets some weight relief with the 2kg claim. Shapes as a leading contender. TOWN CRIER (1) is a last-start winner who can make his presence felt.
